<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1190> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1190" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Vell. 1.14.8; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 42f., 117, 436f. Fighting continued around Mt. Eryx (Polyb. 1.58.1-6; cf. Zon. 8.16). Brundisium and Fregenae were founded this year (Vell. 1.14.8, on Brundisium; cf. Liv. Per. 19)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1159> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1159" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Act. Tr., on Sempronius; Polyb. 1.39.1; Eutrop. 2.23; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 4.9.10; Solin. 27.40; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.14; see Degrassi, 42f., 116, 434f. The Consuls together ravaged the coast of Africa, but lost most of their fleet in a storm while returning to Italy (Polyb. 1.39.1-6; Diod. 23.19; Eutrop. 2.23; Oros. 4.9.10-12; Solin. 27.40; Zon. 8.14). Sempronius celebrated a triumph De Poenis (<i>Act. Tr.,</i> Degrassi, 76f., 548)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10209> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10209" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Poeneis. MRR I.211, Itgenshorst no. 138, Rich no. 137." .
